text: Jacques De Coster (5 January 1945 â€“ 11 November 2022) was a Belgian politician and member of the Socialist Party (SP). He served as a member of the Parliament of the Brussels-Capital Region from 1989 to 1999 and from 2005 to 2009. For the SP, De Coster was elected councilor of Sint-Lambrechts-Woluwe and was chairman of the Public Centre for Social Welfare (OCMW) from 2007 to 2012. De Coster died in Woluwe-Saint-Lambert on 11 November 2022, at the age of 77. ==References== Category:Belgian politicians Category:1945 births Category:2022 deaths
